| Chairbot Walks You Around While You Sit                            |
|   from the stop-using-your-legs-like-a-sucker dept.                |
|   posted by samzenpus on Wednesday June 06, @20:19 (Robotics)      |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/06/2230251     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Gary writes "What do you get when you combine a robot and a chair? The
[1]Hubo FX-1 chairbot, of course. In what is perhaps my favorite robot
design yet, this giant chair with legs looks like it came out of some
ridiculous 80's sci-fi movie or something, but it's very, very real. HUBO
FX-1 is two meters in height, and weighs 150 kg. The person sitting can
control the robot easily using the built in joystick. Each ankle has a
3-axis force/torque sensor which measures the normal force and 2 moments.
Each foot has an inclination sensor which measures the angle of the
slope. Also, the rate gyro and the inclination sensor of the body allow
the device to stabilize itself."

Discuss this story at:
    http://hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/06/2230251

