| Using AI To Train Firefighters                                     |
|   from the why-aren't-you-putting-out-the-fire-dave dept.          |
|   posted by samzenpus on Thursday June 07, @02:37 (Software)       |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/07/0319215              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Roland Piquepaille writes "Computer scientists at the University of
Southern California (USC) have developed [1]DEFACTO, a training program
which uses artificial intelligence (AI) to help firefighters practice
simulated emergency situations. The system is currently used by the Los
Angeles Fire Department. DEFACTO has committees of AI 'agents' which can
create disaster scenarios with images and maps seen in 3-D by the
trainees. The software agents also evaluate the trainees' answers and
help them to take better decisions. As one LAFD captain said, 'You can
see if you're heading toward a mistake much more quickly.' Read more for
additional details about this AI project and a photo of [2]a LAFD Fire
Captain using the system."

Discuss this story at:
    http://slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/07/0319215

