|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/07/1726210          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]P. Rivacy writes "If you recall, last month we discussed Congress's
attempts to [1]outlaw the already illegal NSA wiretaps authorized by the
President. [2]The White House is now using delaying tactics to derail the
passage of that bill. Their tactic is to stall on providing documents
related to the President's warrantless wiretapping program, despite
requests from the Senate Intelligence Committee that is currently
reviewing the proposed legislation. '"Another critical priority for
congressional oversight is government wiretapping of Americans, conducted
under the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act, and, illegally, under
the President's warrantless wiretapping program," Senator Russ Feingold
said. "When the program was finally placed within the FISA process, an
opportunity arose for the Administration and the Congress to move
forward, under the law. Unfortunately, the Administration has yet to
demonstrate a real interest in doing so."'"

