| Microsoft and LG Electronics Sign Linux Covenant                   |
|   from the another-company-of-the-willing dept.                    |
|   posted by Zonk on Thursday June 07, @15:29 (Patents)             |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/07/1731252          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]rs232 wrote with a PC World link discussing [1]another alliance
between Microsoft and a vendor via Linux. The vendor this time around is
electronics maker LG, and marks the fifth company to license unspecified
patents relating to Linux or Linux devices from the OS giant. "'This
agreement is focused only on exchange of patent rights,' said David
Kaefer, general manager of IP licensing at Microsoft. 'The open-source
elements of the deal do utilize a covenant model similar to the Xandros
and Novell deals, but this deal is most similar to recent agreements with
Samsung and Fuji Xerox.' Those deals were signed this year in April and
March, respectively. Both covered general access to intellectual property
contained in patent portfolios and included protection for customers
using Linux-based software."

Discuss this story at:
    http://yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/07/1731252

